-- Ex-Vice President Cheney Released 10 Days After Heart Transplant
-- B y   R o g e r   R u n n i n g e n
-- 2012-04-03T15:05:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/ex-vice-president-cheney-released-10-days-after-heart-transplant.html
Former Vice President  Dick Cheney 
was released from a Virginia hospital today after a March 24
heart transplant operation.  Cheney, 71, left Inova Fairfax Hospital Heart and Vascular
Institute 10 days after the surgery, spokeswoman Kara Ahern
said. He expressed thanks to medical teams and “deep gratitude
to the donor” who remains unknown, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Roger Runningen in Washington at 
